body:
**Describe the bug**
Program throws NPE in `Launcher.prettyPrint()` when the path to the current resource has no parent.

**To Reproduce**

Input:
I think the actual input doesn't matter much because the problem lies in manipulating Strings to create paths instead of using the JDK classes for that purpose. I ran into this bug with the following input:
```java
package nested_generic_class;

import java.util.function.Consumer;

public class Foo implements Consumer<Foo.Bar> {
    enum Bar {
        A, B;
    }

    @Override
    public void accept(Bar bar) {
        System.out.println(bar.name());
    }
}
```

Processing with Spoon:
```java
        Launcher launcher = new Launcher();
        launcher.addInputResource(new VirtualFile(code));
        launcher.getEnvironment().setComplianceLevel(16);
        launcher.getEnvironment().setNoClasspath(true);
        launcher.getEnvironment().setAutoImports(true);
        launcher.getEnvironment().setPreserveLineNumbers(true);
        
        launcher.prettyprint();
```

Output:
```java
Exception in thread "main" java.lang.NullPointerException: Cannot invoke "String.substring(int)" because "resourceParentPath" is null
	at spoon.Launcher.prettyprint(Launcher.java:816)
	at spoon_issues.Main.main(Main.java:27)
```

Note that you can also open a pull request reproducing the issue and reference that, instead of writing additional information here.

**Operating system, JDK and Spoon version used**

* OS: MacOS 12.0.1 (Monterey)
* JDK: 17 - OpenJDK Runtime Environment GraalVM CE 21.3.0 (build 17.0.1+12-jvmci-21.3-b05)
* Spoon version: current Github
